title: Portland Dumpsters
name: Portland Dumpsters
description:
A Map by Kiliii

Portland Area Dumpsters for Food, Building Materials, etc...

Please mark the type of food and forage available (i.e. Organic, Lumber)

properties.name: Big City Produce
properties.description: Posted by KiliiiProduce (not-organic) These guys are amenable to dumpstering, so go during the daytime and be friendly.

properties.name: Bread Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Bread Dumpster, not the best bread, but you can usually score a bunch.

properties.name: Bread/canned goods/free box
properties.description: Posted by Revphil 5420 NE 6th Ave, Portland, OR 97211 hit and miss, sometimes there are cosmetic supplies, sometimes fresh bread, sometimes nothing. on 6th at emerson

properties.name: CCC Bike Shop Free Box
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  free bike shop box, mostly tires

properties.name: City Bikes Free Box
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  bike shop free box, mostly tires, sometimes other stuff. Free tools to borrow during biz hours.

properties.name: Elephant's Delicatessen
properties.description: Posted by Robpstewart 1611 Southeast 7th Avenue, Portland, OR, 97214Mainly Good Bread. The bread is loose on top in the compost bins. There is really good rye bread and whole wheat rolls with nuts and pumpkin seeds.

properties.name: Grand Central Bread Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Great bread, I\'ve gotten some that\'s fresher than in the store.

properties.name: Higher Taste
properties.description: Posted by Butterbits 4512 SE 28th Ave

properties.name: House of Vintage
properties.description: Posted by Reversebackwards Shoes, clothes, bric-a-brac, sometimes full sofas and other large household items. Whatever isn\'t selling. Watch out for glass! Emptied on Wednesday mornings I think

properties.name: Hummus Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Have to climb a fence and sqeeze your arm in, but yum!

properties.name: Limbo Produce Market
properties.description: Posted by Reversebackwards Fruits and Veggies!

properties.name: New Seasons (Sellwood)
properties.description: Posted by Newmy51Good source of bread and produce. Behind a chain-link, locked (but hoppable) fence.

properties.name: New Seasons Division
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Boxes by the back door. They usually seperate it out for you. I find early morning (8ish) is best, but any time works.

properties.name: New Seasons Interstate
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  easy chain to hop, they usually don\'t care, go after 11:30pm!

properties.name: Panera Bread
properties.description: Posted by Robpstewart 4121 NE Halsey St, Portland, OREasy access dumpster in back with tons of good bread and very sweet pastries that aren\'t good for you but they\'re a nice treat once and awhile.

properties.name: Portland Sandwich Co
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  dumpster right on the corner. They usually seperate out the sandwiches that are better, so it\'s obvious when you open it. There are usually bagels in the dumpster a few doors down too.

properties.name: Produce Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus

properties.name: Trader Joe's
properties.description: Posted by Revphil  4218 N.E. Sandy Blvd. Portland ORdumpster is next to building on the side street. usually requires getting dirty. lots of flowers, fruit.

properties.name: Trader Joes Reed
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Trader Joes Dumpster, hear it\'s a good one. Neat Limbo which is good for produce.

properties.name: Wild Oats Market Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Klarsen organic veggies mostly, sometimes organic breads and surprises. frequented by Lewis and Clark students. Closes after 11, but isn\'t a very threatening kind of a place and you can pretty much go whenever you want to; hit or miss.

properties.name: Zupans Belmont Dumpster
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus  Flowers, donuts, veggies, yum!

properties.name: blue parrot coffee
properties.description: Posted by Trolf3323 Huge dumpster with mounds of fresh ground coffee.

properties.name: free outside bike tire pump
properties.description: Posted by Gabrielamadeus not exactly a dumpster, but it has come in handy more than once when biking with a slow leak.
